  "claim_short": "1912.03994 Polish spaces of Banach spaces Question 1 asks whether there is a continuous mapping Phi from P_infty to B preserving the isometry type X_mu = X_Phi(mu). Partial result: for every fixed increasing coordinate representative sequence s_j, on the stratum P_s where the quotient vectors e_{s_j} are linearly independent and dense in X_mu, the pullback Phi_s(mu)(sum a_j e_j)=mu(sum a_j e_{s_j}) is continuous...",
